Class LazyMap<KeyType,ValueType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.TreeMap<KeyType,ValueType>
        • org.apache.taverna.scufl2.api.impl.LazyMap<KeyType,ValueType>
  • Type Parameters:
    KeyType - Type of key
    ValueType - Type of value
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Map<KeyType,ValueType>, NavigableMap<KeyType,ValueType>, SortedMap<KeyType,ValueType>

    public abstract class LazyMap<KeyType,ValueType>
extends TreeMap<KeyType,ValueType>
implements Map<KeyType,ValueType>
    A lazy TreeMap, inspired by org.apache.commons.collections.map.LazyMap

    On get(Object), if a key is not found in the map, getDefault(Object) will be called to create the value for the given key. This value is subsequently inserted into the map before being returned.

    Call TreeMap.containsKey(Object) to check if a key is in the map.

    Implementations of this class must implement getDefault(Object) to specify the default value to create.
